---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { url } from '../config';
---

<Base title="Changelog" description="Release history and version notes for Flux AIO.">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="breadcrumb">
      <a href={url('/')}>Home</a> / <a href={url('/changelog')}>Changelog</a>
    </div>

    <section class="section">
      <h1>Changelog</h1>
      <p class="section-sub">Release history and version notes.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section changelog-entry">
      <h2>v1.7.2 <span class="changelog-date">2026</span></h2>
      <span class="changelog-tag tag-patch">Patch</span>

      <h3>Dashboard</h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li><strong>Energy Tick Sweep Dot</strong> &mdash; A small dot sweeps across the energy bar left-to-right over the 2-second tick cycle, showing exactly when the next energy tick will arrive</li>
        <li><strong>Frame-Rate Timer Bars</strong> &mdash; GCD, Swing, and energy tick animations now update at full frame rate instead of 10Hz for smooth, responsive visuals</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Druid</h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li><strong>Cat: Exposed Tick Tracker</strong> &mdash; Cat&rsquo;s frame-level energy tick tracker is now shared with the dashboard for higher-precision sweep dot positioning (filters Furor/Wolfshead energy)</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section changelog-entry">
      <h2>v1.7.1 <span class="changelog-date">2026</span></h2>
      <span class="changelog-tag tag-patch">Patch</span>

      <h3>Druid</h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li><strong>Bear: Mangle on CD in AoE</strong> &mdash; Swipe AoE now yields to Mangle when it comes off cooldown, maintaining the 30% bleed damage debuff even during multi-target pulls</li>
        <li><strong>Barkskin Form Safety</strong> &mdash; Barkskin middleware no longer fires in bear or cat form, preventing unexpected form drops mid-combat</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section changelog-entry">
      <h2>v1.7.0 <span class="changelog-date">2026</span></h2>
      <span class="changelog-tag tag-minor">Minor</span>

      <h3>All Classes: Polish &amp; Quality Pass</h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li><strong>TTD Gating on Cooldowns</strong> &mdash; Racial abilities and burst CDs now respect the &ldquo;Min TTD&rdquo; setting across all classes, preventing wasted cooldowns on dying targets</li>
        <li><strong>Dashboard Swing Timer</strong> &mdash; All classes now get a swing timer bar by default (no per-class config needed)</li>
        <li><strong>HasBuffs Safety</strong> &mdash; Added <code>or 0</code> guards on buff/debuff checks across all modules for nil-safety</li>
        <li><strong>Dead Import Cleanup</strong> &mdash; Removed unused variables and imports across all 9 class modules</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Druid</h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li><strong>Balance: Innervate</strong> &mdash; New self-Innervate strategy when mana drops below threshold in Moonkin form</li>
        <li><strong>Balance: Proc Optimization</strong> &mdash; Clearcast procs now prioritize Starfire (most expensive spell). Optional Nature&rsquo;s Grace Wrath priority for faster casts during the proc window</li>
        <li><strong>Balance: DoT Refresh</strong> &mdash; Insect Swarm and Moonfire now refresh when expiring regardless of mana tier</li>
        <li><strong>Barkskin Middleware</strong> &mdash; New off-GCD defensive middleware, usable in all forms when HP drops below threshold</li>
        <li><strong>Frenzied Regen Fix</strong> &mdash; Now correctly targets self instead of current target</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Priest</h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li><strong>Discipline: Binding Heal</strong> &mdash; New strategy heals both self and an injured party member simultaneously</li>
        <li><strong>Smite: Inner Focus</strong> &mdash; New off-GCD strategy pairs Inner Focus with Holy Fire or Mind Blast for free casts</li>
        <li><strong>Shadow: Debuff Detection Fix</strong> &mdash; Uses max-rank debuff IDs for reliable VT/SWP/VE detection</li>
        <li><strong>Shadow: TTD Gates</strong> &mdash; VE, VT, and Devouring Plague skip dying targets to avoid wasting GCDs</li>
        <li><strong>Holy: Clearcasting Optimization</strong> &mdash; Free Greater Heal threshold relaxed to 95% (Inspiration proc + mana saved). Inner Focus now pairs with GH threshold</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Rogue</h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li><strong>Stealth Opener Fix</strong> &mdash; All 3 specs: fixed opener logic to work correctly with Vanish re-stealth in combat</li>
        <li><strong>Combat: Expose Armor</strong> &mdash; Now respects energy pooling gate</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Shaman</h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li><strong>Elemental: Opening CL</strong> &mdash; Chain Lightning now available on first cast of combat (LB counter starts ready)</li>
        <li><strong>Elemental: Cast Counter Fix</strong> &mdash; LB/CL counters only increment on successful cast, preventing desync on failed casts</li>
        <li><strong>Enhancement: Burst Tags</strong> &mdash; Racial and Fire Elemental now tagged as burst abilities for /flux burst</li>
        <li><strong>Restoration: Spell Target Fixes</strong> &mdash; Earth Shield and Mana Tide now have correct spell_target for prerequisite checks</li>
        <li><strong>Tremor Totem Fix</strong> &mdash; Auto-tremor setting now properly checked before activation</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Warlock</h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li><strong>CoA Refresh Threshold</strong> &mdash; Curse of Agony refresh threshold changed from 0 to 0.1s to prevent rare double-cast</li>
        <li><strong>Racial Burst Tags</strong> &mdash; All 3 specs: Racial abilities now tagged as burst and respect TTD gating</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Warrior</h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li><strong>Protection: Execute</strong> &mdash; New Execute strategy for targets below 20% HP (rage-efficient finisher)</li>
        <li><strong>Protection: Demo Shout Fix</strong> &mdash; Now targets player (AoE shout) instead of target unit</li>
        <li><strong>Bloodrage</strong> &mdash; No longer tagged as burst (it&rsquo;s a sustained rage generator, not a cooldown)</li>
        <li><strong>Death Wish &amp; Recklessness</strong> &mdash; Now respect Min TTD setting</li>
        <li><strong>Unused Spell Cleanup</strong> &mdash; Removed unused stance actions, potion actions, and debuff constants</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Paladin</h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li><strong>Healing Scan Fix</strong> &mdash; Fixed potential nil error when party/raid size exceeds pre-allocated target pool</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Mage</h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li><strong>Improved across all 3 specs</strong> &mdash; Various rotation refinements for Fire, Frost, and Arcane</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Hunter</h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li><strong>Code Cleanup</strong> &mdash; Removed unused imports and streamlined class module</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section changelog-entry">
      <h2>v1.6.9 <span class="changelog-date">2026</span></h2>
      <span class="changelog-tag tag-minor">Minor</span>

      <h3>Druid: Bear Tab Targeting Settings &amp; Manual Target Respect</h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li><strong>Configurable Tab Targeting</strong> &mdash; Three new settings: Min Priority to Tab (All/Elites+/Bosses Only), Max Mobs to Manage (2-8), and Spread Lacerate toggle</li>
        <li><strong>Manual Target Respect</strong> &mdash; Tab targeting now detects manual target changes (clicking enemies, teammates) and backs off for 3 seconds, preventing the rotation from overriding intentional player targeting</li>
        <li><strong>Feral Charge Awareness</strong> &mdash; Won't swap off an out-of-range target when Feral Charge is available, allowing gap-close plays</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section changelog-entry">
      <h2>v1.6.8 <span class="changelog-date">2026</span></h2>
      <span class="changelog-tag tag-minor">Minor</span>

      <h3>Druid: Bear Threat Management</h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li><strong>Growl Fix</strong> &mdash; Uses UnitThreatSituation API for reliable aggro detection instead of relying solely on targettarget. Added 1.5s grace period on pull to prevent taunting immediately after Feral Charge opener</li>
        <li><strong>Smart Tab Targeting</strong> &mdash; Tab targeting now prioritizes boss &gt; elite &gt; trash when picking up loose mobs. Cycles AUTOTARGET until landing on the desired target (max 10 attempts)</li>
        <li><strong>Dead Target Swap</strong> &mdash; Automatically switches off dead targets to find a new one</li>
        <li><strong>Out-of-Range Swap</strong> &mdash; When current target moves out of melee, scans for the best in-range target by priority instead of blind tab targeting. Aborts mid-cycle if desired target leaves melee</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>All Classes: Combat Time Context</h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li><strong>context.combat_time</strong> &mdash; Added raw combat time (seconds) to the shared context, available to all classes</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section changelog-entry">
      <h2>v1.6.7 <span class="changelog-date">2026</span></h2>
      <span class="changelog-tag tag-minor">Minor</span>

      <h3>Druid: Sapper Charge Powershift</h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li><strong>Sapper Shifting</strong> &mdash; Cat powershifts now optionally use Goblin/Super Sapper Charges via DMH instant-cast macros when facing 3+ enemies or bosses</li>
        <li><strong>Settings</strong> &mdash; Two new checkboxes under Cat &gt; Powershift: &ldquo;Use Super Sapper Charge&rdquo; and &ldquo;Use Goblin Sapper Charge&rdquo; (both off by default, requires DMH addon)</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Paladin: Seal of Wisdom Mana Recovery</h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li><strong>Low Mana Seal Swap</strong> &mdash; Protection automatically switches to Seal of Wisdom when mana drops below threshold (default 20%) for passive mana recovery</li>
        <li><strong>Mana Conservation</strong> &mdash; During low mana mode, Exorcism and Hammer of Wrath are skipped, Consecration limited to 2+ targets</li>
        <li><strong>Item Fix</strong> &mdash; Fixed Item Click definitions causing C_Item.IsEquippableItem errors on consumables</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>All Classes: Boss Detection</h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li><strong>Shared context.is_boss</strong> &mdash; Added boss detection to the shared context object, available to all classes. Fixed bear lacerate spread using undefined is_boss_fight field</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section changelog-entry">
      <h2>v1.6.6 <span class="changelog-date">2026</span></h2>
      <span class="changelog-tag tag-minor">Minor</span>

      <h3>Shaman: Elemental Mastery + Chain Lightning Combo</h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li><strong>EM Hold for CL</strong> &mdash; Elemental Mastery now waits until Chain Lightning is off cooldown before firing, ensuring the guaranteed crit lands on CL (highest value spell) instead of a Lightning Bolt</li>
        <li><strong>EM Override</strong> &mdash; When EM buff is active, Chain Lightning fires immediately regardless of rotation type setting (consumes the crit optimally)</li>
        <li><strong>Toggle</strong> &mdash; &ldquo;Hold EM for Chain Lightning&rdquo; checkbox in Elemental &gt; Cooldowns, enabled by default</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Shaman: Mana Conservation</h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li><strong>Elemental Stop Shocks</strong> &mdash; New &ldquo;Stop Shocks Mana%&rdquo; slider (default 30%) &mdash; stops Flame Shock, Earth Shock, and movement shocks when mana is low, preserving mana for Lightning Bolt</li>
        <li><strong>Enhancement Stop Shocks</strong> &mdash; Same slider for Enhancement (default 30%) with SR exemption &mdash; mana gate is bypassed when Shamanistic Rage is active or off cooldown</li>
        <li><strong>Shamanistic Focus</strong> &mdash; Enhancement now prioritizes Earth Shock when the Shamanistic Focus proc is active (melee crit = 60% cheaper shock), using the free shock immediately</li>
        <li><strong>SR Mana% Default</strong> &mdash; Shamanistic Rage trigger threshold raised from 30% to 50% to match reference rotation</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Shaman: Flame Shock TTD Gate</h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li><strong>Min TTD</strong> &mdash; New &ldquo;Flame Shock Min TTD&rdquo; slider (default 12s) for both Elemental and Enhancement &mdash; prevents wasting mana applying a 12s DoT on targets that will die before it ticks out</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section changelog-entry">
      <h2>v1.6.5 <span class="changelog-date">2026</span></h2>
      <span class="changelog-tag tag-minor">Minor</span>

      <h3>Shaman: Priority Interrupt Scanner</h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li><strong>Nameplate Scanning</strong> &mdash; New priority interrupt system scans nearby nameplates (20yd) for dangerous NPC casts (heals, AoE, CC) and automatically tab-targets to interrupt them, then returns to your original target</li>
        <li><strong>38 Priority Spells</strong> &mdash; Covers TBC dungeon and raid dangerous casts: healing (Dark Mending, Greater Heal, etc.), AoE (Blast Nova, Arcane Explosion, etc.), and CC (Polymorph, Domination, etc.)</li>
        <li><strong>Toggle Setting</strong> &mdash; &ldquo;Priority Interrupt (Scan)&rdquo; checkbox in General &gt; Utility, enabled by default</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Shaman: Fire Nova TTD Gate</h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li><strong>AoE Totem TTD</strong> &mdash; Fire Nova and Magma Totem AoE drops (Elemental &amp; Enhancement) now respect the CD Min TTD setting, preventing wasted totems on dying targets</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>All Classes: CD Min TTD Setting</h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li><strong>New Setting</strong> &mdash; Added &ldquo;CD Min TTD&rdquo; slider to all class schemas &mdash; prevents trinkets and major cooldowns from firing on targets that will die before the CD pays off</li>
        <li><strong>Trinket Gate</strong> &mdash; Shared trinket middleware now checks cd_min_ttd before firing offensive trinkets</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Shaman: Quality of Life</h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li><strong>Major Mana Potion</strong> &mdash; Added Major Mana Potion as fallback when Super Mana Potion is unavailable</li>
        <li><strong>Fire Elemental Protection</strong> &mdash; Rotation now detects active Fire Elemental Totem and won&rsquo;t overwrite it with other fire totems</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section changelog-entry">
      <h2>v1.6.4 <span class="changelog-date">2026</span></h2>
      <span class="changelog-tag tag-patch">Patch</span>

      <h3>Dashboard Refinements (All Classes)</h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li><strong>Layout Reorder</strong> &mdash; Target info and threat bar moved below Buffs, directly above Debuffs for better visual grouping</li>
        <li><strong>CP Label</strong> &mdash; Combo point pips now have a &ldquo;CP&rdquo; label matching the GCD/Swing bar style</li>
        <li><strong>Lighter Timer Labels</strong> &mdash; GCD and Swing bar text uses shadow instead of heavy outline for a cleaner look</li>
        <li><strong>Consistent Separators</strong> &mdash; All section dividers now use the same inset and opacity</li>
        <li><strong>Opaque Background</strong> &mdash; Dashboard background is now fully opaque</li>
        <li><strong>Smaller Icon Text</strong> &mdash; Reduced icon overlay font to prevent text bleeding outside icon frames</li>
        <li><strong>Bottom Clipping Fix</strong> &mdash; Increased frame padding to prevent debuff icons clipping at the bottom edge</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section changelog-entry">
      <h2>v1.6.3 <span class="changelog-date">2026</span></h2>
      <span class="changelog-tag tag-patch">Patch</span>

      <h3>Dashboard Polish (All Classes)</h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li><strong>Section Separators</strong> &mdash; Subtle divider lines between Cooldowns, Buffs, and Debuffs sections for clearer visual grouping</li>
        <li><strong>Buff Active Borders</strong> &mdash; Active buffs now show a gold border; inactive buffs use a dim border</li>
        <li><strong>Threat Bar</strong> &mdash; Threat percentage is now a color-coded progress bar (green/orange/red) below the target info instead of inline text</li>
        <li><strong>Combo Point Pips</strong> &mdash; Visual combo point indicators for Druid (Cat) and Rogue, replacing the old text display</li>
        <li><strong>Icon Text Shadow</strong> &mdash; Drop shadow on icon overlay text for improved readability</li>
        <li><strong>Collapsible Debuffs</strong> &mdash; Debuff section hides automatically when no target exists and all tracked debuffs are target-based</li>
        <li><strong>Dimmer Idle States</strong> &mdash; &ldquo;Idle&rdquo; and &ldquo;N/A&rdquo; text uses a subtler color to reduce visual noise</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Bug Fixes</h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li><strong>Timer Bar Overflow</strong> &mdash; Fixed GCD and Swing timer bars extending outside the dashboard frame when resetting</li>
        <li><strong>Range Infinity Crash</strong> &mdash; Fixed integer overflow when <code>GetRange()</code> returns infinity</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section changelog-entry">
      <h2>v1.6.2 <span class="changelog-date">2026</span></h2>
      <span class="changelog-tag tag-patch">Patch</span>

      <h3>Bug Fixes (All Classes)</h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li><strong>Trinkets Not Firing</strong> &mdash; Fixed trinket middleware passing invalid texture arguments to Show(), preventing offensive and defensive trinkets from activating</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section changelog-entry">
      <h2>v1.6.1 <span class="changelog-date">2026</span></h2>
      <span class="changelog-tag tag-patch">Patch</span>

      <h3>Bug Fixes (All Classes)</h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li><strong>Position Persistence</strong> &mdash; Settings button and combat dashboard now correctly remember their dragged position across game reloads. Fixed a timing issue where the framework database wasn&rsquo;t ready when position restore ran</li>
        <li><strong>Range Detection</strong> &mdash; Simplified target range calculation in the shared context builder</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section changelog-entry">
      <h2>v1.6.0 <span class="changelog-date">2026</span></h2>
      <span class="changelog-tag tag-minor">Minor</span>

      <h3>New Features (All Classes)</h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li><strong>Combat Dashboard</strong> &mdash; Real-time overlay showing current priority, cooldown readiness, buff/debuff tracking, resource bar, and GCD + swing/wand timer bars. Toggle via <code>/flux status</code> or the <em>Show Dashboard</em> setting</li>
        <li><strong><code>/flux</code> Slash Commands</strong> &mdash; <code>/flux burst</code> (force offensive CDs for 3s), <code>/flux def</code> (force defensive CDs for 3s), <code>/flux gap</code> (fire best gap closer), <code>/flux status</code> (toggle dashboard), <code>/flux help</code> (command list)</li>
        <li><strong>Burst Context System</strong> &mdash; Auto-burst conditions: during Bloodlust/Heroism, on pull (first 5s), in execute phase (&lt;20% HP), or always in combat. Configure per-class via checkboxes</li>
        <li><strong>Movable Settings Button</strong> &mdash; Settings button can now be dragged anywhere on screen instead of being locked to the minimap perimeter. Position persists across reloads</li>
        <li><strong>Dynamic Swing/Wand Timers</strong> &mdash; Dashboard timer bar automatically detects equipped weapon type: shows Swing for melee weapons, Wand/Shoot for ranged</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Class-Specific Dashboard Configs</h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li>Each class has tailored cooldown icons, buff/debuff tracking, and custom lines (e.g., Warrior stance display, Shaman totem states, Hunter pet HP, Rogue combo points)</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section changelog-entry">
      <h2>v1.4.0 <span class="changelog-date">2026</span></h2>
      <span class="changelog-tag tag-minor">Minor</span>

      <h3><a href={url('/classes/druid')} class="class-link c-druid">Druid</a></h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li>Bear: Added tab targeting for threat management &mdash; cycles through nearby enemies to spread threat</li>
      </ul>

      <h3><a href={url('/classes/priest')} class="class-link c-priest">Priest</a></h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li>Shadow: Fixed pre-combat pull sequence &mdash; Vampiric Touch before SW:P</li>
        <li>Shadow: Fixed debuff detection for SW:P and Vampiric Embrace</li>
        <li>Shadow: Added wand auto-attack as filler when no other spells available</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section changelog-entry">
      <h2>v1.3.1 <span class="changelog-date">2026</span></h2>
      <span class="changelog-tag tag-patch">Patch</span>

      <h3><a href={url('/classes/mage')} class="class-link c-mage">Mage</a></h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li>Arcane: Trinkets and racial cooldowns now suppressed during conserve phase &mdash; they are held for the next burn window instead of wasted on low-value casts</li>
      </ul>

      <h3><a href={url('/classes/paladin')} class="class-link c-paladin">Paladin</a></h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li>Retribution: Hammer of Wrath now skipped when mana is critically low (&le;1000) &mdash; rotation strips to Seal of Blood + Crusader Strike + Judgement only</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section changelog-entry">
      <h2>v1.3.0 <span class="changelog-date">2026</span></h2>
      <span class="changelog-tag tag-minor">Minor</span>

      <h3><a href={url('/classes/druid')} class="class-link c-druid">Druid</a></h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li>Bear: Fixed Demoralizing Roar detection to use spell ID array &mdash; now correctly detects debuffs applied by other Druids</li>
        <li>Caster: Fixed nil guard on Innervate buff check; unified rejuv/regrowth checks with shared utilities</li>
      </ul>

      <h3><a href={url('/classes/mage')} class="class-link c-mage">Mage</a></h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li>Arcane: Simplified burn/conserve cycle tracker &mdash; now uses <code>ab_stacks</code> natively, no separate counter; conserve&rarr;burn transition now allows &le;1 stack instead of requiring 0</li>
        <li>Arcane Filler now correctly checks <code>ab_stacks</code> at max before triggering (was broken with old counter)</li>
        <li>Remove Curse middleware now scans all party members, not just self</li>
      </ul>

      <h3><a href={url('/classes/paladin')} class="class-link c-paladin">Paladin</a></h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li>Holy: Added configurable Divine Illumination mana threshold (default 60%)</li>
        <li>Holy/Protection: Added Racial strategies &mdash; Arcane Torrent (mana restore) and Stoneform (defensive), off-GCD</li>
        <li>Holy: Judgement only fires when no emergency targets exist (previously blocked when any target was below 80%)</li>
        <li>Protection: Added Mocking Blow &mdash; 2-min CD taunt fallback when in Battle Stance (smart filter: elites/bosses only, healer protection)</li>
        <li>Healing pool pre-allocated at load time &mdash; fixes potential in-combat table allocation</li>
      </ul>

      <h3><a href={url('/classes/priest')} class="class-link c-priest">Priest</a></h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li>Discipline: Prayer of Healing minimum injured group count is now configurable (default 3, range 2&ndash;5)</li>
        <li>Holy: Renew/Greater Heal HP threshold now uses the <code>holy_renew_hp</code> setting instead of a hardcoded value</li>
      </ul>

      <h3><a href={url('/classes/rogue')} class="class-link c-rogue">Rogue</a></h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li>Subtlety: Added Ghostly Strike strategy &mdash; secondary builder on cooldown, grants +15% dodge for 7s</li>
        <li>Subtlety: Preparation now only fires when Shadowstep is actually talented (not on every spec)</li>
        <li>Assassination/Subtlety: Rupture refresh window is now configurable (default 2s)</li>
        <li>Shiv now bypasses the energy pooling gate &mdash; Deadly Poison refresh takes priority even while pooling for the next finisher</li>
      </ul>

      <h3><a href={url('/classes/shaman')} class="class-link c-shaman">Shaman</a></h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li>Enhancement: Moved Windfury and Fire Nova Totem twists before Stormstrike/Shock &mdash; time-sensitive totem management now fires correctly</li>
        <li>Restoration: Earth Shield now checks <code>is_spell_available</code> (only fires when 41pt Restoration talent is learned)</li>
      </ul>

      <h3><a href={url('/classes/warlock')} class="class-link c-warlock">Warlock</a></h3>
      <ul class="features">
        <li>Life Tap fallback strategy now mirrors the <code>life_tap_mana_pct</code> middleware threshold &mdash; no longer fires at 90% mana as a last resort</li>
      </ul>

      <h3><a href={url('/classes/warrior')} class="class-link c-warrior">Warrior</a></h3>
